                            <comment id="19108" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 17 Aug 2006 08:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done - email addresses are now only visible to logged-in users (which should be good enough). Actually we meant to do this for a long time but somehow never got around to do it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19109" author="jetforme" created="Thu, 17 Aug 2006 08:33:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the amazingly fast response! My only concern is that it is ridiculously easy to get a login. There&apos;s no CAPTCHA, not even an email verification. A spambot could easily exist to automatically log in to JIRA sites...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to mark this bug still open, because I don&apos;t know if you&apos;ll see this comment otherwise. Please feel free to close it. Thanks again!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19110" author="jetforme" created="Thu, 17 Aug 2006 08:35:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess I spoke too soon...I don&apos;t know how to reopen this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19141" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 19 Aug 2006 10:40:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Point taken... I changed the visibility to &quot;hidden&quot;. Let&apos;s see if someone complains, in particular for what reason &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
